summary: This is an email chain from March 2011 regarding the management and shipment of completed investigation sections from an office to the Miami (MM) office due to space constraints. It includes a list of file numbers and case agents, and requests permission to ship the files.

events.title: Deadline to approve file shipment
events.description: The email requests a response by the close of business on Thursday, March 24, 2011, regarding whether completed investigation sections can be shipped to the Miami (MM) office.

keyFacts: The document is an internal email chain about administrative logistics for pending investigations.
It references a need to ship 'completed sections' of investigations to the Miami office due to running out of space.
A specific file number is mentioned: 31E-MM-108062 - EFTA02730470.
The correspondence indicates a standard procedure for file retrieval via email to 'OS' with a two-day turnaround.
No named individuals, victims, or specific events related to criminal activity are detailed in this excerpt.
